description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated, enthusiastic and dynamic individual with a proven national record of implementing and spreading innovations and improvements to provide real-world, strategic, high value impact for patients and the public&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe that the successful implementation is crucial within an organisation and across boundaries, particularly when such new and creative ideas add value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join a motivated team, responsible for implementation and spread of improvements and innovations across Cardiff and Vale University Health Board and beyond, building on the outstanding work of staff and wider partners in the face of the Covid pandemic, and moving us closer to the powerful vision of A Healthier Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“&lt;/em&gt;Local innovation is essential, but it is not enough on its own. Good practice must scale up to regional and to national levels, in a systematic way, and at pace.” A Healthier Wales: our plan for health and social care 2019&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud that our system have made progress on a wide range of areas, and we have seen an outstanding commitment and engagement of our staff in the face of the Covid challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moving forward we know we have much still to do - our commitment to our patients and passion for delivering the very best care to all is unwavering. We recognise that it is only by continuing to focus on transformation through collaborative implementation and rapid spread of great ideas and improvements that we will achieve our ambitious vision for the future of our Health Board, our patients and our Community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an individual able to demonstrate experience of leading and managing implementation and spread of innovations and improvements, gained within organisations of wide ranging scale and complexity. We are looking for a skilled communicator, able to inspire our people and collaborators across organisational boundaries. The successful candidate will be adept at setting and achieving ambitious targets, implementing and spreading solutions designed to add value against a context of tight financial constraints and intense regulatory and public scrutiny.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jonathon Gray&lt;br /&gt;jonathon.gray@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Bricknell &lt;br /&gt;Helen.Bricknell@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
